    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We actually used to do this, many years and mono versions ago.\n\nBack then mono's bundling tools didn't work properly on OSX, so I wrote an abomination that recursively copied and patched the libraries we needed to run OpenRA ([link for the curious](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/4c8575b1f53d5bff8b2e92e905dfe2f982f8c9f3/packaging/osx/package.sh)).\n\nWe threw that away at some point because 1) it was horrible, 2) it was hard to justify an OSX-specific packaging step when we were able to automate the rest of our packaging on a Linux box, and 3) it added ~15 MB to our installer download, which was a big deal back when the entire rest of the game was only 2MB and hosted off a single server with limited bandwidth.\n\nNone of these reasons are relevant now of course, but I haven't been in any rush to revisit those experiences :wink:\n\nWe eventually moved back to a native-code OSX launcher, which lives in its own repository: http://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRALauncherOSX.  In principle you just need to tweak the Makefile to link against and package a local mono framework.  Would you be interested in taking a shot at this?\n"
  },
