    "body": "I'd rather download 15mb then a gig ;)\n\nVery interesting, looking at your OpenRALauncher makefile, is libgdiplus.dylib all that is required of the whole Mono.framework?  surely that alone can be bundled.  I've used a commandline tool called dylibbundler which would  copy all the linked dylibs from the executable to the app bundle, and sort through all the dll he*\\* re-linking everything together.  I'm sure a similar approach could be put in.  It's a little more cleaner, robust, and versatile then your script (Although that is some really nice scripting done there!).\n\nhttps://github.com/auriamg/macdylibbundler\n"
  },
