    "updated_at": "2016-10-23T12:43:11Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The `libgdiplus.dylib` symlink is there to work around missing/incorrect paths defined in the mono standard library.  Life would be much simpler if that was the only dependency, but it isn't.\n\nmacdylibbundler appears to cover the native assembly rewriting (the `patch_mono` function in my old script), but we also need to change the references in the managed assembly metadata (the *.config files).\n\nMono's \"official\" procedure is to use their Xamarin.Mac framework, which then has a build task that compiles down to a .app bundle.  I haven't tested this, so it's not clear whether this uses a bundling tool that we could repurpose, or, more likely, AOT compiles everything down to native code (which we couldn't repurpose).\n\nResurrecting my old script is probably going to be the easiest option if we want to do this.\n"
  },
